{{Quote|I loved being a witch.|Lilia Calderu|Death's Hand in Mine}}
'''Lilia Calderu''' was a [[Sicily|Sicilian]] witch specializing in divination. Raised in [[Lilia Calderu's Coven|a coven]] in Sicily, Calderu predicted that they would be wiped out by a fever but they accepted their fates. Emigrating to the [[United States]], she met [[William Kaplan]] at his bar mitzvah and put a sigil on him, which was then tied to [[Billy Maximoff]] after he transferred his soul to Kaplan's dead body.

[[2026|Three years later]], she met Maximoff and [[Agatha Harkness]], who sought to recruit her into a coven to walk the [[Witches' Road]]. During the [[Divination Witch Trial]], Calderu began experiencing more gaps than usual that led her to speak with her late [[Lilia Calderu's Maestra|Maestra]] during her first lesson. Coming to terms with her powers, she successfully completed the trial but sacrificed herself to defeat the [[Salem Seven]] by inversing gravity in the trial room, impaling them and herself on the ceiling's swords.

==Biography==
===Early Life===
{{Expand}}
Lilia Calderu was raised as part of a [[Lilia Calderu's Coven|coven of witches in Sicily]], where she studied the craft from [[Lilia Calderu's Maestra|her Maestra]].{{Ref|AAA107}} Calderu correctly foretold that her coven would be wiped out by a fever. In her subsequent travels, Calderu's powers of divination repeatedly predicted tragedy.{{Ref|AAA102}}

===Meeting William Kaplan===
{{Quote|Your lifeline is broken in two."<br>"What? That can't be good."<br>"It can mean many things. It often represents personal growth and important life changes. You're becoming a man. A new you. I wouldn't worry.|Lilia Calderu and [[William Kaplan]]|Familiar by Thy Side}}
In [[2023]], Calderu was hired for [[William Kaplan]]'s bar-mitzvah party. When the young boy approached her palm-reading stand, Calderu questioned him by asking whether he was looking behind or ahead, to which the boy answered that he was looking ahead. As Calderu started looking at his palm, he spoke up, saying he did not want to know too much. Realizing he startled Calderu, he apologized. Calderu stated that his journey is one of great transformation. She then stopped abruptly as the lights flickered. She soon spoke up, saying his life line was split in [[Wiccan|two]].

However, Calderu assured William that it could mean a lot of things, not just bad. It could simply mean it was a new him. Calderu then stopped again, saying the tower was reversed. A confused William said she was supposed to be reading his palm. A worried Calderu apologized, saying she remembered something. Getting worried himself, William left, saying he should get back to the party. However, he complimented the stand design. Calderu reached out for his hand, simply telling William to pay attention to his life now.

Once William left, Calderu conjured a [[Glossary|sigil]], prohibiting William from revealing his identity to any witch. Calderu placed the sigil inside William's coat, and the sigil's effect was instant. She told a guest to return the coat to the teenage boy who entered her tent.{{Ref|AAA106}}

===[[Walking of the Witches' Road|Walking the Witches' Road]]===
====[[Search for Coven Members#Lilia Calderu|Recruited by Agatha Harkness]]====
Over the next three years, Calderu continued to work on her [[Madame Calderu's Psychic Readings|business]] in [[Westview]]. However, in late [[2026]], she was visited by [[Agatha Harkness]] and a mysterious teen boy. The two were in search of a Divination witch for their coven. Harkness pretended Teen was her son and that she was trying to find a stash of gold her late husband had hidden. She made Teen pay for a reading, during which Calderu falsely informed Harkness that the gold would be found in her husband's closet. However, the psychic then had a real divination, telling Harkness that she had been a thrall to another for three years.

Realizing her ruse was up, Harkness talked to Calderu about the [[Witches' Road]] and asked her to join her, but Calderu said that no witch in her right mind would join Harkness' coven given her reputation, claiming that she was the reason that people thought witches poisoned apples and ate babies, to which Harkness responded that babies were delicious. Harkness tried to appeal to Calderu by complimenting her, stating she didn't look a day over 450, which only offended Calderu. Harkness tried to persuade Calderu by telling her she could be her old self again, but Calderu still refused.

However, the divination witch did use her powers to make a list of the witches that would be in Harkness' coven, and to her surprise, her name was on the list, she exclaimed "Three of Pentacles." Harkness said it was a sign, and Teen gave Calderu Harkness' address, telling her to be there by five that afternoon.{{Ref|AAA102}}

====Entering the Witches' Road====
Later that evening, Calderu arrived at Harkness' [[Agnes O'Connor's House|house]], where she met the rest of the coven [[Jennifer Kale]], the Potions witch, whom she dubbed as "The High Priestess." and [[Alice Wu-Gulliver]], the protection witch. The group realized they did not have a green witch, Lilia stated that there was a missing member that represented the black heart. Harkness recruited [[Sharon Davis]] and the witches performed [[Ballad of the Witches' Road]] to conjure it. However, it did not work initially and Calderu realized it was just Harkness' attempt to steal their powers. The gate is opened and the coven barely escapes from [[Salem Seven]].{{Ref|AAA109}}

The group entered the road and removed their shoes out of respect for the road, they soon started their walk. As they walked the Road, the coven discussed their situation, wondering what they would be up against for their trials. Believing Harkness had already walked the Road, they asked her, so she answered that each trial would test their respective skills. The coven learned of the sigil put on Teen, which Harkness knew nothing about, and returned focus to reaching the end of the Road. After they nearly lost Davis to quicksand, Harkness reminded the coven that the first rule was to never step off of the Road.{{Ref|AAA103}}

====[[Potions Witch Trial]]====
The [[Agatha Harkness' Coven|coven]] turned around to see a [[Witches' Road Beach House|mansion]] appear on the [[Witches' Road]]. Once the coven was inside, they noticed their clothes had been changed to resemble a coastal chic style. The first trial began with the coven all drinking a bottle of wine that was provided for them, Calderu was unknowingly posioned along with her coven, their faces became swollen except for Harkness. Calderu once again said something out of context, confusing the group. The swelling went down, and [[Jennifer Kale]] was able to deduce that they had been poisoned by [[Alewife's Revenge]]. 

Kale needed to brew an antidote for them, being their [[:Category:Potions Witches|potions witch]]. Kale instructed the coven with ingredients she required, with Calderu and Agatha retrieving zooplankton in petroleum products for her. One of the effects of the poison was hallucinations, Lilia had a vision of her younger self leading her to her [[Lilia Calderu's Maestra/Witches' Road|Maestra]] being taken by [[Death]]. Calderu snapped out of it and cried out in her native language. Later on, Calderu stated "Try to save Agatha!" which sparkee Agatha's intesret,.All the two were able to find were Kale's [[Kale Kare|skin care products]], which were supposedly organic, but Harkness suspected otherwise, and decided to call Kale's bluff about her products. The coven all found their items, but noticed that the mansion was now submerged and slowly beginning to fill with water.

Kale started brewing the antidote, where Harkness was successful in exposing Kale for her products not being all-natural. They finished the brew, each giving a strand of their hair, but it did not work. Kale panicked andHarkness told her that despite always hating her, she respected the work that Kale did. Kale was able to remember the final ingredient, Teen's blood, and they drank the antidote, healing them of the poison. Passing the test, the oven opened up for them to escape as water rushed in, and although Calderu advised them against going in, due to a friend of her perishing this way, they decided to anyways. Though most of the coven were able to drink it in time, they were unable to save [[Sharon Davis]], who died as they escaped the trial through the oven.{{Ref|AAA103}}

====Summoning a Green Witch====
Following the death of Mrs. Davis, the coven decided it was necessary to find a substitute Green Witch, but Harkness argued against this, informing her coven that she was the only witch that made it out of the Road last time. Harkness suggested they summon a new green witch, although Calderu was worried something could go wrong. Using [[Teen]]'s spell book, they performed an incantation, and summoned [[Rio Vidal]], who burst out of Davis' grave. The new member identified herself as not just ''a'' Green Witch, but ''the'' Green Witch. With Vidal tagging along as an ally, the coven reached the [[Protection Witch Trial]]. {{Ref|AAA103}}

====[[Protection Witch Trial]]====
The [[Agatha Harkness' Coven|coven]] spotted a [[Witches' Road Recording Studio|Recording Studio]], which made [[Alice Wu-Gulliver]] turn in the other direction. Wu-Gulliver did not want to enter, but the [[Witches' Road]] moved the house in front of them, forcing them to go inside. Once they entered, their clothes were once again changed, now influenced by the [[1970s]], Calderu studied her surroundings, looking for clues, but she was saddened to see illustrations of the methods used to kill witches in the past. Wu-Gulliver joined her and they spoke about [[Lorna Wu]] and her attempts to open the Road while performing with her fans, however, Calderu once again dissociated from the present and exclaimed two sentences one that warned Alice and the other showed her asking wether she's wispy or kooky, Wu-Gulliver replied that she's a bit of both.

Due to [[Agatha Harkness]]'s trickery, the witches overheard Vidal stating that Harkness would kill them all and Vidal would collect their corpses, but their confrontation was interrupted by the teen starting a record of Lorna Wu's version of the "[[Ballad of the Witches' Road]]" that played backwards, transferring the [[Wu Family Curse]] onto the other members of the coven. Calderu was attacked first, her shoulders burned as Alice quickly cast a protection circle around her. Wu-Gulliver recognized its effects after it struck Calderu and Kale, and she began apologizing for her involvement when the curse threw the teen through a glass pane, though he seemed largely unharmed. The group performed Lorna's rendition of [[Ballad of the Witches' Road]] after Wu-Gulliver realized that it was a protection spell. Calderu contributed with different instruments and her vocals. Theey were successful at killing the curse, passing the trial, but Teen passed out from his injury.

Returning to the Road, Harkness panicked over the teen's state, Calderu exclaimed "Three of Swords."" upon seeing it. Jennifer Kale was only just able to save him after they returned to the road, Calderu remarked that what Kale did was very impressive. and Calderu, Wu-Gulliver, Kale, and Vidal bonded while Harkness watched over him, until Vidal and Harkness split from the group after Vidal alluded to their shared past. Calderu started a sentence and once again she stopped, causing the group to laugh at her condition.{{Ref|AAA104}}

====[[Ambush on Agatha Harkness' Coven|Escaping the Salem Seven]]====
The [[Agatha Harkness' Coven|coven]] rested on the road, but Calderu suddenly woke up, revealing that the Salem Seven is in the vicinity, arriving on the road through a gate left open by the summoning spell that brought [[Rio Vidal]]. They confronted Harkness and Calderu explained to the group the Salem Seven's vendetta against the covenless witch. They moved, however they find themselves surrounded, [[Teen]] suggested they us a hexenbesen to escape. Calderu disliked the idea, but with no other option, she paired up with Kale to perform the ritual.

As they got prepared, [[Owl]] appeared, followed by the rest of the Seven. Luckily, the coven lifted off into the night sky. Calderu stated she hadn't flown in centuries. Their enjoyment was brief, however, as they were soon sucked back down towards the road. Although they crashed into [[Vertigo]], they were able to escape into the [[Witches' Road Cabin]]. {{Ref|AAA105}}

====[[Spirit Witch Trial]]====
The [[Agatha Harkness' Coven|coven]] entered a [[Witches' Road Cabin|cabin]], which changed their clothes into pajamas. Harkness told them that they were safe from the [[Salem Seven]], so all they needed to do was complete the trial. [[Rio Vidal]] stated that they were in Harkness' trial. Calderu pointed out the blood moon outside, stating that this is when the veil between the living and the dead is at its thinnest. [[Teen]] assumed that communing with the dead was Lilia's speciality, but she quickly corrected him. They figured out that they needed to commune to the dead, and Teen found a Ouija board, which started the trial.

Teen read out the rules, emphasizing the one about not taunting the dead. The coven gathered around the board, wondering who from Harkness' past they would be speaking with. Hesitantly, Harkness joined the coven but manipulated the board to make it seem like they were communing with the spirit of [[Sharon Davis]]. Harkness pretended to be possessed by Davis, speaking in her voice, Lilia wanted to soothen the situation, but the coven caught on to her act. Vidal called out Harkness for being scared, and she sat back down with the coven to use the board properly. The board said that it was "Death" and that it wanted to punish Harkness.

Harkness let go of the board, which flew off the table and released the spirit, posessing Harkness in the proccess. The coven discussed how they could punish Harkness, figuring that it would end the trial. Harkness was freed from the possession, and the spirit introduced herself as [[Evanora Harkness]], she told the coven that they must complete the [[Witches' Road]] without Agatha. Calderu and the group were about to leave, when Wu-Gulliver stepped in to release Harkness from Evanora's control. Calderu said "Knight of Wands." upon witnessing the scene, Agatha ended up draining Wu-Gulliver's powers, killing her in the proccess.

The coven left the trial, with the exception of [[Death|Vidal]], Lilia reminded the group that death comes for everyone. Teen's identity is revealed by Harkness, enraged by her, he is the son of the [[Scarlet Witch]], [[Wiccan|Billy Maximoff]]. The teenager used his powers and took control over Calderu and Kale. The two dragged Harkness and threw her off the road. Once they were relseased from Maximoff's control, he threw them off the road as well.

====[[Divination Witch Trial]]====
{{Quote|You may not know this about the [[Witches' Road|Road]], but when you successfully complete a trial, like I just did, it's not a good idea... to overstay your welcome. Usually, something terrible happens. Disaster, destruction, sudden upheaval. Like the Tower, upright.|Lilia Calderu to the [[Salem Seven]]|Death's Hand in Mine}}
Shortly after sinking in the mud, Calderu and [[Jennifer Kale|Kale]] found themselves in a tunnel system under the [[Witches' Road]]. Calderu's mind traveled and experienced her final moments out of sequence, she was falling through a black void, dressed up in a gown and dress similar to that of Glinda the Good Witch, from the ''Wizard of Oz.'' Lilia woke up before Kale, noticing a mysterious figure approaching her. Calderu asked who she was, so she revealed herself, it was [[Death|Rio Vidal]], now in her form as Death, telling her that all roads led to her. 

Upon Vidal's departure, Calderu received insight from her future self and quickly informed Kale about what happened and gave her clear instructions to find the next trial. Kale was confused but figured she was telling the truth. The two encountered the way out of the Witches Road, but Lilia inspired her to keep going on, they quickly evade the [[Salem Seven]]. While making their way through the tunnels, Calderu and Kale bond, with Calderu explaining her condition, she experienced her life out of sequence. In this moment, some of her randomized comments are given context. Eventually, Calderu and Kale overhear voices behind shelving. They push through the shelf and fall into the next [[Divination Witch Trial|trial]], which happened to be Lilia's.

The trial took place inside a [[Witches' Road Castle|castle]] and involved a Tarot spread, with swords dangling from the ceiling. Calderu and Kale arrived just in time, as Harkness and Maximoff caused the ceiling to lower. Calderu took Maximoff as the subject for her spread, she also told him that she was "cool" with him, despite his previous attack. However, swords still fell, including one that was going to hit Calderu, so Harkness quickly tackled her out of danger. Calderu once again traveled through her memories and found herself back in her younger self's body. She spoke to her [[Lilia Calderu's Maestra|Maestra]], who helped her recollect herself and learn what her true purpose is. She realized that she will indeed fall, prompting her Maestra to ask what she will do with her remaining time.

After that, Calderu realized that she is the subject, so she began to read for herself, she is the Traveler, represented by the Queen of Cups, it worked, no swords fell down. She continued by placing the following cards, Three of Pentacles, The Knight of Wands, High Priestess, Three of Swords, Tower Reversed, each card representing part of her journey. As Calderu placed the cards, the ceiling continued to lower, forcing them all to crouch down with only seconds left until they were killed. The final card, which equaled to Lilia's destination, was Death. Harkness placed the final card for Calderu, completing the trial. Calderu realized that [[Rio Vidal]] was Death, which Harkness confirmed. The [[Salem Seven]] arrived, so they escaped from the castle. Calderu told her coven to exit through the Iron Maiden, she returned Maximoff's spell book, told Harkness to drop to the ground after being called a coward and lastly she reminded Kale she was the path ahead, after she refused letting Calderu stay behind.

When all of her coven members left the trial, Calderu spoke to the Salem Seven, reminding them that whoever stays behind after a trial is completed, they may suffer from the consequences. Lilia stated some of the outcomes and used the Tarot spread to her advantage, flipping the Tower Card, dubbing it the Tower Upright. The castle turned upsidedown, Lilia and the Salem Seven fell to their demise, being impaled by the swords on the ceiling. However, Calderu finally accepted her fate and found peace after experiencing her whole life out of order.{{Ref|AAA107}}

